// Battery C — Write-action tool-execution honesty (v0.6.3.4 guardrail)
// Tests that Mistral calls write-action tools rather than narrating
// completion without actually firing them ("Done, I've indexed it" with
// no corresponding tool call).
//
// The v0.6.3.4 honesty guardrail shipped in 143861f but was never
// separately swept. This battery validates it across the three write-
// action tools most prone to narration-before-execution: documents.index,
// memory.capture, and reminders.set.
//
// Expectation: tool_called — the runner checks that the named tool
// appears in the SSE tool_start events. If Mistral narrates "Done"
// without firing the tool, tool_start never emits and the case fails.
//
// NOTE: documents.index queries may route through the lazy-index path
// (project.read over-cap -> fire-and-forget after response). If a
// documents.index case fails with tool-not-called, check the server
// log for a lazy-index line before assuming narration-before-execution.
// The runner catches hard failures (tool never called at all); the
// server log catches timing (narration before vs after tool result).
//
// Run with server logs tailed:
//   grep -E "tool|index|memory|reminder|narration" from the server terminal
